# API Integration Guidelines

## API Structure
- Use Axios for HTTP requests
- Implement proper error handling
- Use TypeScript for API types
- Follow RESTful conventions
- Implement proper request/response interceptors

## API Organization
- Keep API calls in `services/api` directory
- Use `endpoints.ts` for route definitions
- Implement proper API versioning
- Use environment variables for API URLs
- Implement proper request caching

## Data Handling
- Implement proper data validation
- Use TypeScript interfaces for API responses
- Handle loading states
- Implement proper error messages
- Use proper data transformation

## Authentication
- Implement proper token management
- Handle token refresh
- Implement proper logout
- Use secure storage for tokens
- Implement proper session management

## When to Apply
- When implementing new API endpoints
- When refactoring existing API calls
- When handling API errors
- When implementing authentication
- When reviewing API security